title: The Beast: When Eddie met Arnie
des: The World's strongest man, Eddie 'THE BEAST' Hall has reached the pinnacle of his career and finds himself at a crossroads in his life. Despite his immense achievements, Eddie suffered from bouts of depression throughout his career, and now is in a place where he can no longer continue in the sport that saved him from himself. In danger of falling back into the dark world of depression Eddie looks for a new channel of expression, and turns to his life-long hero and friend, Arnold Schwarzenegger, in the hope that he can follow him into the acting world of Hollywood. The story begins with Eddie's humble beginnings in Stoke-on-Trent, England, where as a young man he battled depression, and how with the support of his family he overcame the roller coaster of emotional, physical and mental challenges of competitive sport to rise to the top of the Strongman world. Now, on a quest for a new challenge, Eddy travels to Arnie's roots in Austria, to his own record breaking events in Australia, and finally, having met up with his friend Arnie in Ohio, to Los Angeles, where he encounters the ruthless world of talent agents and directors, as he tries to break into the most competitive business of all......Hollywood.
cast: Arnold Schwarzenegger, Gabriel Luna, Eddie Hall, Alex Needham

title: My Sweet Buttercup
des: A Mother's memories keep her sane as she fights through the grief of loosing of her youngest daughter, Jessica in a car accident and questioning her faith after making a sacrifice for her daughter's happiness. Jessica goes on a weekend trip with her Godmother, Chelsey and Nicole, Chelsey's foster daughter and Jessica's best-friend to attend an annual college Homecoming game to Alabama. Their journey back to Texas ends with no one returning home. Jessica's grieving Mother Bridget fights privately to keep her sanity and publicly to display a broken faith in her God. The memories of Jessica's multiple circles of friends weave a blanket of comfort around Bridget as she battles to see memories of Jessica while pushing away anger. Bridget fights to be a support to her other children and Chelsey and Nicole's families. This story is inspired by true events that left hundreds grieving from Texas to Virginia. A movie that will unveil the realism of grief, faith, tears and hope. A character has been removed for legal purposes.
